Lucien Barnes, Respondent v. James R. Keene, Appellant. Decided June 27, 1890. Appeal from judgment entered in favor of the plaintiff upon the verdict of a jury, and from an order denying defendant’s motion for a new trial. . Shipman, Barlow, Larocque & Choate, for appellant. S. H. Randall, for respondent.

Before Freedman and Truax, JJ.

Per Curiam.

Judgment and order affirmed with costs.
